<HEADLINE>
<P>
OSCAR MEMORIES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The clips from the Akira Kurosawa movies showed a bunch of people being shot 
with arrows and some nice young women being cruelly killed off. 
</P>
<P>
For me as a viewer, and I'm sure for other viewers, these scenes were painful 
and just plain pointless. 
</P>
<P>
The whole attitude involved -- that by showing man's inhumanity to man you make 
us all better -- is really boneheaded. All it does is give people nightmares. 
</P>
<P>
Let's quit acting like Kurosawa is teaching people something they don't already 
know. Grossing people out to make a humanitarian point is like punching someone 
in the stomach to try to explain that being hit is painful. 
</P>
<P>
JOHN SIMONS 
</P>
<P>
Long Beach 
</P>
