<TEXT>
<P>
A new feature, the Los Angeles Times Interview, debuts in today's Opinion 
section. Mario Vargas Llosa, Peruvian novelist and presidential candidate in 
today's election, talks about the differences between being a writer and being 
a politician. M3 
</P>
