<HEADLINE>
<P>
QUESTIONING 'FAITH' 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The correct term for the plight of the runaways in Livingston, Mont., is 
spiritual abuse. Unfortunately, Americans have so little language for spiritual 
realities other than that provided by institutional religions that spiritual 
abuse goes unrecognized not only in this extreme case but in millions of 
American homes. 
</P>
<P>
If it were adults who were being forced into the spiritual practices described, 
it would be grounds for revolution. But because they are young adults, they 
forfeit our collective protection. Perhaps some good can come from this if test 
cases do result, and the pain of spiritual abuse for children is exposed and 
made conscious. At the very least, the state must stop enforcing the obedience 
of children to parents who are spiritually violating them. 
</P>
<P>
DIANA QUINN ROSE, Los Angeles 
</P>
</TEXT>
