<HEADLINE>
<P>
GRAND OPENING: IN HILLS OF ANAHEIM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Crowne Summit opens today in the hills of Anaheim, featuring 24 two-story 
attached houses priced from $250,000 to $350,000. 
</P>
<P>
The three- and four-bedroom townhouses by Boulevard Development Inc. are 
available in three floor plans ranging in size from 1,484 to 1,900 square feet 
and have tile roofs, up to three bathrooms, rear-yard fencing and front-yard 
landscaping. 
</P>
<P>
Move-ins are scheduled to begin in late July and the homeowners association fee 
is $161.18 a month. The project is near Anaheim Hills, but is outside the 
boundaries of that planned development. 
</P>
<P>
The sales office is open daily from 10 a.m. to 5 p.m. at 803 Shanada Court, 
reached from the southbound Imperial Highway exit of the Riverside (91) 
Freeway. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<CORRECTION-DATE>
<P>
April 15, 1990, Sunday, Home Edition 
</P>
</CORRECTION-DATE>
<CORRECTION>
<P>
FOR THE RECORD 
</P>
<P>
In the hills -- Crowne Summit, a 24-unit townhouse development by Boulevard 
Development Inc. is in Anaheim Hills. The project at 803 Shanada Court has its 
own association dues of $161.18 a month. 
</P>
</CORRECTION>
