<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSWIRE: MICHAELS MAY BREAK WITH ABC 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
As a result of the firing of Brent Musburger by CBS, Al Michaels has taken the 
first step in an attempt to break his contract at ABC Sports and move to CBS, 
the Washington Post reported Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
Attorneys for Michaels Friday filed for arbitration with the American 
Federation of Television and Radio Artists in Los Angeles, claiming the network 
breached his contract when it suspended him without pay for a nepotism incident 
in February. 
</P>
<P>
Michaels has three years remaining on a contract that industry sources say is 
worth $1.5 million to $2 million annually. 
</P>
<P>
The suspension was meted out after Michaels' teenage daughter was hired as a 
messenger during ABC's broadcast of the U.S. Figure Skating Championships in 
Salt Lake City, according to reports. ABC officials have refused to confirm the 
suspension. 
</P>
</TEXT>
