<HEADLINE>
<P>
CRITICS' CHOICE: CHEKHOV'S SISTER BY W. D. WETHERELL (LITTLE, BROWN: $16.95; 
288 PP. 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Roberta Smoodin 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
"The novel is beautifully, lyrically written, and in its questioning of what 
both art and reality are, its form as well as its content voice its concerns." 
Roberta Smoodin 
</P>
</TEXT>
