<HEADLINE>
<P>
CANDIDATES FOR TUSTIN'S CITY COUNCIL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
One of the major issues brought out by most of the candidates for the Tustin 
City Council is the chaotic, circus-like atmosphere of our council meetings. 
They are right on target. 
</P>
<P>
The most troublesome part of this situation, however, is that three of the 
candidates, John Kelly, Berklee Maughan and Carole Bryand have actively 
participated in creating this atmosphere, have said that they like the way the 
council has been running, and that they intend to generate more of the same if 
elected. 
</P>
<P>
The last thing our city needs is more clowns trying to keep the circus going. I 
would hope that people will take the time to vote on April 10, and to vote for 
candidates we can be proud of: candidates who will restore a professional and 
adult atmosphere to the serious business of running a city. 
</P>
<P>
GREGG LYNCH 
</P>
<P>
Tustin 
</P>
