<HEADLINE>
<P>
ALLEGATIONS AGAINST ORANGEWOOD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
We foster parents who take children into our homes directly from Orangewood 
Children's Home want to take this opportunity to reply to the March 31 Times 
article listing allegations against Orangewood. 
</P>
<P>
In comparing Orangewood and foster care as it is run by our county's Social 
Services, we feel that they rank with the very best programs and facilities 
nationwide. 
</P>
<P>
Orangewood Children's Home has served as a model for development of other 
children's centers throughout the state and has been honored by the President. 
</P>
<P>
We have seen Social Services' response to public concerns about the care of our 
county's children and that they constantly try to make the changes to improve 
conditions. 
</P>
<P>
We also live in reality, however, and understand that in a large bureaucracy 
such as Orange County Social Services, there are bound to be occasional 
injustices. The measure of the problem is what response and corrective action 
is taken. 
</P>
<P>
We support the system and feel confident that Social Services is working hard 
to meet the needs of individual children. 
</P>
<P>
RUTH HANNING 
</P>
<P>
Yorba Linda 
</P>
<P>
 This letter was also signed by 16 other foster parents. 
</P>
<P>
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Letter to the Editor 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA040890-0142 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 201432 </DOCID>
