<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
FRESNO'S WOLF TAKES BITE OUT OF UC IRVINE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Steve Wolf struck out 10 and walked none to lead Fresno State to a 2-1 victory 
over UC Irvine in a Big West Conference baseball game at Fresno Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
Mike Noel scored when Chris Gonzales hit into a double play to give Fresno 
State (25-11, 5-0 in conference) a 1-0 lead in the first inning. 
</P>
<P>
Irvine (23-15, 1-4) tied it in the fourth, when Ray Walker and Chris Gallego 
hit back-to-back doubles. 
</P>
<P>
In the bottom of the inning, Todd Johnson hit a one-out double and Jeff 
Borgesse hit a grounder to the hole that bounced off shortstop John Damush's 
arm, allowing Johnson to score from second. 
</P>
<P>
In California Collegiate Athletic Assn. baseball: 
</P>
<P>
Chapman 6, Cal Poly San Luis Obispo 2 -- Tom Allison had four hits and scored 
twice and Mike Giuseffi had four hits, scored and had two RBIs for visiting 
Chapman (22-13, 12-5). 
</P>
<P>
In nonconference men's tennis: 
</P>
<P>
San Diego 5, UC Irvine 2 -- Nineteenth-ranked San Diego (20-4) upset No. 14 
Irvine (14-10) at San Diego. Richard Lubner defeated J.R. Edwards, 7-6, 6-1, 
for Irvine. 
</P>
<P>
In nonconference women's tennis: 
</P>
<P>
UC Irvine 9, San Jose State 0 -- Stacy Cadigan defeated Patty Cornelius, 6-2, 
6-3, to lead visiting Irvine (7-18). 
</P>
<P>
In Big West Conference softball: 
</P>
<P>
Cal State Fullerton 1-3, Hawaii 0-0 -- Yvette Hernandez scored on Malia Ouzts' 
single in the seventh to lead Fullerton over host Hawaii (13-21, 3-15) in the 
first game. In the second game, Missy Coombes had one hit, scored and had an 
RBI for Fullerton (32-9, 12-3). 
</P>
<P>
In pool play of the Cal State Hayward softball tournament: 
</P>
<P>
Chapman 1, Southern Utah 0 (8 innings) -- Jackie Blake (16-3) pitched a 
one-hitter for Chapman (32-12). In an earlier game, Cal State Hayward defeated 
Chapman, 6-3. Hayward converted two walks, an error and a single into three 
runs in the third. 
</P>
<P>
In Golden State Athletic Conference softball: 
</P>
<P>
Azusa Pacific 5-4, Southern California College 0-1 -- Lisa Todd had a 
three-hitter, striking out 12, for host Azusa Pacific in the first game. 
</P>
<P>
In National Assn. of Intercollegiate Athletics softball: 
</P>
<P>
Cal Lutheran 8-4, Christ College Irvine 0-0 -- Tracy Schultz doubled for one of 
Christ College Irvine's (20-17, 7-7) two hits in the first game. 
</P>
</TEXT>
