<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP ROUNDUP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In the Beaumont Invitational track meet: 
</P>
<P>
Junior Renee Wright was named athlete of the meet for leading the Orange 
Lutheran girls' team to an easy victory. Wright won the 100-meter hurdles 
(15.6), the 300-meter hurdles (47.63) and anchored two winning relay teams: the 
400 relay (52.4) and the 1,600 relay (4:31.72). 
</P>
<P>
Orange Lutheran scored 134 points and Temecula Valley was second with 64 1/2. 
</P>
<P>
In Woodbridge softball tournament pool play: 
</P>
<P>
El Toro 1, Bolsa Grande 0 -- Marta Bickert pitched a no-hitter, struck out six 
and walked two for the Chargers (13-5) at Harvard Park in Irvine. Bickert (3-2) 
also picked up an RBI with a single to center in the second inning, bringing 
home Jennifer Jourdan, who had walked and reached second on a wild pitch. 
Bickert, a junior, had two hits, as did teammate Kymm Maniscalco. 
</P>
<P>
Trabuco Hills 4, Huntington Beach 2 -- Wendy Pike (3-1) pitched a five-hitter 
for the Mustangs (11-5). 
</P>
</TEXT>
