<HEADLINE>
<P>
PEACHES CAN MAKE GREAT SIDE DISHES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Add canned cling peaches to your repertory of side dishes for pretty and 
nutritious accompaniments to your favorite roasted meats. Hot stuffed cling 
peach halves are a pretty and delicious garnish for a roast. 
</P>
<P>
Simply drain the peaches, reserving the liquid for another use, and place in a 
shallow baking pan. Fill each peach with cranberry sauce and sprinkle with 
cinnamon sugar. Heat under the broiler until bubbly. 
</P>
<P>
Or stuff peach halves with chutney if the dinner menu calls for roast pork, 
with creamy horseradish for roast beef or with mint jelly for roast lamb. 
</P>
<P>
To brighten up frozen peas when served with meat loaf, chicken or pork, heat 
them with canned cling peach slices and 1/2 teaspoon crushed dried mint leaves. 
Drain and stir in 1 tablespoon butter or margarine before serving. 
</P>
<P>
Or warm turkey slices in liquid drained from canned cling peach slices. Stir in 
3 to 4 tablespoons butter or margarine, 2 tablespoons capers and 2 tablespoons 
lemon juice. Heat until bubbly. Add peach slices and heat through. Serve over 
parsley rice for an inviting dinner entree. 
</P>
</TEXT>
