<HEADLINE>
<P>
THREAT FROM DROUGHT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
It has occurred to me that the water shortage is not the fault of the public's 
using too much water. I agree we should not use water unwisely during these 
times. 
</P>
<P>
My question to the city councils and the Board of Supervisors: Why do you let 
this happen? 
</P>
<P>
As elected officials, your job is not to cave in to builders, city or county 
staff, and investment groups that say in their EIRs that there is plenty of 
water for now and all times. From now on, the EIR should include, "What effect 
will the added use of water have on the residents of our area?" It should have 
statements from the water providers saying that there will be enough water. 
</P>
<P>
I call on all the people to call on their councilmen, local boards, planning 
commissioners and ask them why they allowed this to happen. 
</P>
<P>
LEO E. NICHOLS 
</P>
<P>
Port Hueneme 
</P>
</TEXT>
