<P>
</P>
<P>
</P>
<P>
New Cabinet Department 
</P>
<P>
By a vote of 161 to 266, the House rejected a White House-backed amendment 
limiting the scope of a new Cabinet-level Department of Environmental 
Protection. The House then sent the bill (HR 3847) to the Senate by a wide 
margin. 
</P>
<P>
The amendment sought to kill language subjecting federal polluters to the same 
hazardous waste laws that apply to private firms. It also attempted to put 
under White House control a new bureau set up to increase public access to data 
on pollution, and to eliminate other areas where the Cabinet department would 
wield more power than the EPA now has. 
</P>
<P>
Members voting yes wanted to limit the scope of the new department. 
</P>
