<TEXT>
<P>
SCOTT BAILES 
</P>
<P>
Age: 27 
</P>
<P>
Position: Pitcher 
</P>
<P>
Major league experience: Four years 
</P>
<P>
How obtained: Acquired from Cleveland in exchange for infielder Jeff Manto and 
pitcher Colin Charland, Jan. 9, 1990. 
</P>
<P>
Pertinent stats: Has a career 31-41 record and 4.70 earned-run average in four 
seasons at Cleveland, where he was a starter and reliever. 
</P>
<P>
Comments: If Bailes can pitch against other teams the way he pitched against 
the Angels last season, the left-hander will be a valuable addition. Bailes 
struggled against most opponents, but had little trouble with the Angels, 
allowing one earned run and striking out eight in 13 innings for a 2-0 record. 
General Manager Mike Port says Bailes, primarily a fastball-curveball pitcher, 
has shown flashes of brilliance this spring, but he needs to become more 
consistent. It appears his role will be middle to long relief. 
</P>
</TEXT>
