<P>
MARK EICHHORN 
</P>
<P>
Age: 29 
</P>
<P>
Position: Pitcher 
</P>
<P>
Major league experience: Three years, 112 days 
</P>
<P>
How obtained: Signed as free agent, Dec. 19, 1989. 
</P>
<P>
Pertinent stats: Was successful at triple-A Richmond last season, going 1-0 
with a 1.32 ERA and 19 saves, but struggled at Atlanta. 
</P>
<P>
Comments: Eichhorn has had a history of shoulder problems but when healthy, the 
right-hander who has a side arm, Kent Tekulve-like delivery, can be effective 
against right-handed hitters. He had two good seasons at Toronto in 1986 and 
'87 but has spent most of his 11-year professional career in the minor leagues. 
He will be used as a set-up man in late-inning situations. 
</P>
