<TEXT>
<P>
Since I do not have children, I seldom watch the Charlie Brown TV specials. 
</P>
<P>
Fortunately, however, I read in the newspaper of the unique nature of the show 
aired on March 16, "Why, Charlie Brown, Why?" And special it was indeed! How 
thankful I am that I did not miss it. The sensitivity, compassion and 
tenderness conveyed through the story of little Janice, the leukemia patient, 
was almost overwhelming. I found myself falling in love with these characters 
and am not at all embarrassed to admit that they moved me to tears. 
</P>
<P>
This was a shining example of television at its finest and is one program that 
should be replayed many times. 
</P>
<P>
Ann Latham Agreda, Los Angeles 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Letter to the Editor 
